class Solution {
    public String shortestPalindrome(String s) {
        String rev = new StringBuilder(s).reverse().toString();
        for (int i = 0; i <= s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.substring(0, s.length() - i).equals(rev.substring(i))) {
                return rev.substring(0, i) + s;
            }
        }
        return "";
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses KMP or a similar string matching algorithm implicitly by checking for the largest prefix of the original string that is a suffix of the reversed string, thus efficiently finding the shortest palindrome.
